observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the interest of the Municipality should at all times be protected, all provisions of law, rules and regulations pertaining to procurement should be strictly adhered to. We further recommended that:
a. A comprehensive Annual Procurement Plan should be prepared based on the Annual Budget. No procurement shall be undertaken unless it is in accordance with the approved APP;
b. Notices of Award and Notices to Proceed must be posted within the required time frame;
c. The Municipal Engineer should monitor and inspect all completed projects during the one (1) year defects liability period to determine any defects for correction by the concerned contractors and to issue the Final Certificate of Acceptance after one year from project completion date and to require the concerned contractor to post the required warranty bond in accordance with Section 62.2.3 of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184.
d. The TWG should be created by the BAC;
e. Observers from duly recognized private group must come from an association of constructors duly recognized by CIAP.
f. Post-qualification process should not be completed within one day and not more than twelve (12) calendar days from the determination of the Lowest Calculated/Highest Rated Bid.
g. Direct the BAC to prepare the Procurement Monitoring Report in the form prescribed by the GPPB and submit to the GPPB the duly approved report in printed and electronic formats within 14 calendar days after the end of each semester in compliance with Section 12.2 of the IRR of RA No. 9184.

We recommend to management:
Prioritize the reconciliation of the inventory count with the property and accounting records;
Continuously analyze the reconciling items in the PPE account and accordingly prepare correcting journal entries to reflect the correct balances of the affected accounts;
Adopt a uniform valuation of  properties;
Reclassify to proper inventory account tangible assets with estimated useful life of more than one year but small enough to be considered and recorded as PPE. An Inventory Custodian Slip (ICS) shall be prepared upon  issuance of tangible items for monitoring, control and accountability.

